Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.function

Interface IntRelation

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface IntRelation
    Verifies that two integers have a certain relationship to each other. For example, if A equals 5 B equals 3, then the relationship X greater than Y exists between these integers. (An equally appropriate name would be IntBiPredicate, an interface not present in the java.util.function package}.)
    Author:
    Ayco Holleman
